<document xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:z="http://www.ebi.ac.uk/z" source="Whatizit"><text><SENT sid="0" pm="."><plain><z:e sem="disease" ids="C0024796" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="MFS|MFS1">Marfan's syndrome</z:e> (MS) is an <z:e sem="disease" ids="C0019247" disease_type="Disease or Syndrome" abbrv="">inherited disease</z:e> of connective tissue </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="1" pm="."><plain>The most characteristic ocular change is dislocation of lens, but <z:hpo ids='HP_0000545'>myopia</z:hpo> and <z:hpo ids='HP_0000541'>retinal detachment</z:hpo> also can occur </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="2" pm="."><plain>We examined 11 MS patients using electroretinography (ERG) </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="3" pm="."><plain>6 cases showed <z:mpath ids='MPATH_458'>normal</z:mpath> ERG </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="4" pm="."><plain>5 cases had <z:hpo ids='HP_0000512'>abnormal ERG</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="5" pm="."><plain>One had <z:hpo ids='HP_0000541'>retinal detachment</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="6" pm="."><plain>3 had <z:hpo ids='HP_0000545'>myopia</z:hpo> and 1 case suffered from secondary <z:hpo ids='HP_0000501'>glaucoma</z:hpo> </plain></SENT>
<SENT sid="7" pm="."><plain>The defects of visual function were shown by electrophysiological test in those MS patients </plain></SENT>
</text></document>